  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Rinse the baby pak koi and pat them dry with paper towels.",
    "Heat the coconut oil in the lacquerware bowl over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, and ginger, and cook until fragrant, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the cinnamon, cayenne pepper, nutritional yeast, kombu powder, and tapioca starch, and stir to combine.",
    "Add the baby pak koi and cook for 2-3 minutes, or until they start to soften.",
    "Pour in the soy milk and maple syrup, and stir to combine.",
    "Transfer the bowl to the preheated oven and bake for 15-20 minutes, or until the pak koi are tender and the sauce is bubbly and slightly caramelized.",
    "Remove the bowl from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes before serving."
  ],
